suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid argument.

suggestion.Solution: [step] If the source model framework is Caffe, try again with a valid [--weight] argument. [step] If the source model framework is not Caffe, try again with a valid [--framework] argument.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], and [--dynamic_dims] are mutually exclusive.

suggestion.Possible Cause: [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], and [--dynamic_dims] are mutually exclusive.
suggestion.Solution: [step] In dynamic shape scenarios, include only one of these options in your command line. [step] In static shape scenarios, remove these options from your command line.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for [--log] is invalid. Must be selected from [debug], [info], [warning], [error], and [null].

suggestion.Possible Cause: The [--log] argument is invalid.
suggestion.Solution: Valid values include [debug], [info], [warning], [error], and [null].

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Argument [%s] for [--input_shape] is invalid. Shape values must be positive integers. The error value is: %s.

suggestion.Possible Cause: In static shape scenarios, set the shape values of each input node in the [--input_shape] to positive integers.
suggestion.Solution: [step] In static shape scenarios, set the shape values in [--input_shape] to positive integers. [step] In dynamic shape scenarios, add the related dynamic-input option in your command line, such as [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims].

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, but the dimension count of the dynamic-shape input configured in [--input_shape] is less than 1.

suggestion.Possible Cause: As [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, the dimension count of the dynamic-shape input configured in [--input_shape] must not be 0.
suggestion.Solution: [step] In static shape scenarios, remove the [--dynamic_batch_size] option from your command line. [step] In dynamic shape scenarios, set the corresponding axis of the dynamic-shape input in [--input_shape] to –1.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for [--%s] is out of range.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The argument is out of range.
suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid argument.

suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid node name.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for shape [%s] is invalid. When [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, only batch size N can be –1 in [--input_shape].

suggestion.Possible Cause: When [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, only batch size N can be –1 in the shape.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: When [--dynamic_image_size] is included, only the height and width axes can be –1 in in [--input_shape].

suggestion.Possible Cause: When [--dynamic_image_size] is included, only the height and width axes can be –1 in the shape.
suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid [--input_shape] argument. Make sure that axes other than height and width are not –1.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for [--dynamic_image_size] is invalid. Must be formatted as [imagesize1_height,imagesize1_width;imagesize2_height,imagesize2_width].

suggestion.Possible Cause: In the [--dynamic_image_size] argument, each profile must have two dimensions.
suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid [--dynamic_image_size] argument. Make sure that each profile has two dimensions.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Directory for [--%s] is too long. Keep the length within %s.

suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid directory.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Directory [%s] for [--%s] does not include the file name

suggestion.Solution: Add the file name to the directory.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The [--singleop] argument is not a proper directory.
suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid argument.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Failed to open file [%s] specified by the [--singleop] argument.

suggestion.Possible Cause: Failed to open the file specified by the [--singleop] argument.
suggestion.Solution: Check the owner group and permission settings and ensure that the user who runs the atc command has enough permission to open the file.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: File [%s] specified by [--singleop] is not a valid JSON file. Reason: %s.

suggestion.Possible Cause: Failed to parse the file specified by the [--singleop] argument in JSON format.
suggestion.Solution: Check that the file is in valid JSON format.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Empty Op name in the file specified by the [--singleop] argument.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The file specified by the [--singleop] argument contains an unnamed Op.
suggestion.Solution: Check that no Op name is empty in the file.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [%s] and [%s] for tensor indexed [%s] of Op [%s] are invalid in the file specified by the [--singleop] argument.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The file specified by the [--singleop] argument contains invalid tensor attributes.
suggestion.Solution: Try again with valid tensor dtype and format.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Attribute name of Op [%s] is empty in the file specified by the [--singleop] argument.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The file specified by the [--singleop] argument contains an unnamed attribute.
suggestion.Solution: Check that no Op attribute name is empty in the file.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Attribute name [%s] of Op [%s] is invalid in the file specified by the [--singleop] argument.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The file specified by the [--singleop] argument contains an empty attribute.
suggestion.Solution: Check that no Op attribute value is empty in the file.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, but none of the nodes specified in [--input_shape] have a batch size equaling –1.

suggestion.Possible Cause: As [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, ensure that at least one of the nodes specified in [--input_shape] has a batch size equaling –1.
suggestion.Solution: [step] In static shape scenarios, remove the [--dynamic_batch_size] option from your command line. [step] In dynamic shape scenarios, set the corresponding axis of the dynamic-shape input in [--input_shape] to –1.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Nodes (for example, [%s]) connected to aipp must not be of type fp16. Check the [--insert_op_conf] and [--input_fp16_nodes] options in your atc command line.

suggestion.Possible Cause: Do not set dtype to fp16 for a node connected to aipp.
suggestion.Solution: [step] To enable AIPP, remove the nodes connected to aipp from the [--input_fp16_nodes] argument. [step] If AIPP is not required, remove the [--insert_op_conf] option from your atc command line.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: The [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument has [%s] profiles, which is less than the minimum [%s].

suggestion.Possible Cause: The number of configured profiles is less than the minimum.
suggestion.Solution: Ensure that the number of profiles configured in the [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument is at least the minimum.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] has [%s] profiles, which exceeds the maximum [%s].

suggestion.Possible Cause: The number of configured profiles exceeds the maximum.
suggestion.Solution: Ensure that the number of profiles configured in the [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument does not exceed the maximum.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: The profiles configured in the [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument have inconsistent dimension counts. A profile has %s dimensions while another has %s dimensions.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The configured profiles have inconsistent dimension counts.
suggestion.Solution: Ensure that the profiles configured in the [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument have the same dimension count.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Dimension size [%s] is invalid. Must be greater than 0.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The shape values of each profile must be positive.
suggestion.Solution: Set the shape values of each profile to positive in the [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: The [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument have duplicate profiles.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The configured profiles must be unique.
suggestion.Solution: Check that the profiles configured in the [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument are unique.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: As the [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument is included, the corresponding nodes specified in [--input_shape] must have –1 axes.

suggestion.Possible Cause: In dynamic shape scenarios, the corresponding shape value in the input node must be set to –1.
suggestion.Solution: [step] In static shape scenarios, remove the [--dynamic_batch_size] option from your command line. [step] In dynamic shape scenarios, set the corresponding axis of the dynamic-shape input in [--input_shape] to –1.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Failed to load the model from [%s]. Check the model file or the [--framework] argument.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The model file is invalid.
suggestion.Solution: [step] Check that the model file is valid. [step] Check that the [--framework] argument matches the actual framework of the model file.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: The available memory is [%s KB], which is less than the required minimum [%s KB].

suggestion.Possible Cause: Auto Tune requires at least 2 GB available memory.
suggestion.Solution: Stop unnecessary processes and ensure that at least 2 GB system memory is available. Alternatively, change a machine with 2 GB or more of available memory.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: The number of –1 axes overflow for data [%s] with shape [%s].

suggestion.Possible Cause: [--dynamic_dims] is included for more than one input, but the number of –1 axes in the [--input_shape] argument does not match the dimension count per profile in [--dynamic_dims].
suggestion.Solution: Ensure that the number of –1 axes in the [--input_shape] argument matches the dimension count per profile in [--dynamic_dims].

error_info_list.ErrMessage: The number of –1 axes of data [%s] with shape [%s] is greater than the dimension count per profile.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The number of –1 axes in the [--input_shape] argument is greater than the dimension count per profile in [--dynamic_dims].
suggestion.Solution: Ensure that the total number of –1 axes in the [--input_shape] argument is less than the dimension count per profile in [--dynamic_dims].
